    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Popular drying oil used as a paint medium; hardens over several weeks as components of the oil polymerize to form an insoluble matrix.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000039561/Tate Gallery, Completing the Picture (1982)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aceite secante muy utilizado como medio de pintura. Se endurece en varias semanas en la medida que los componentes del aceite se polimerizan para formar una matriz insoluble.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een veelgebruikte, drogende olie die als oplosmiddel in verf wordt gebruikt; verhardt in de loop van enkele weken wanneer delen van de olie polymeriseren en een onoplosbaar bindmiddel vormen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
